# Burla Ephemeral Dev VM

For Burla agent tasks, never edit the primary checkout directly. First create or reopen a linked task worktree, move into it, and only then use the `scripts/dev_vm_*.sh` workflow. Prefer the Burla dev-VM skill and the `scripts/dev-worktree/*.sh` helpers over ad hoc `git worktree`, `gcloud`, `ssh`, or `scp` commands.

Never ask the user which agent slot to use. Pick the lowest-numbered slot under `../burla-worktrees/agent-<id>/` that is missing or contains no task subdirectories. If every existing slot is in use, create the next sequential slot (`agent-05` after `agent-04`, etc.); the VM scripts provision the new GCP project and SSH key automatically.
